Our first material for however long it takes us to finish this series will be 괴양이 (Monster Cat), a story about a man who rescues a dying kitten he names "Caesar" only for it to become... too strong.

By this meeting date, our goal is to have read 2 episodes (화) for the sake of accountability. What we'll do during this meeting is still up in the air, but some options are story discussion, Q&As and popcorn reading of the next episode.

node.title: Celebrating Lunar New Year - dinner and traditional game (optional potluck)
node.description:
Today is considered a new year on lunar calendar (also known as Chinese new year, but that's somewhat inconsiderate to other countries which use the same calendar). Let's get together and celebrate the "new" year!

* I'll have 떡국ddeokguk ready (rice cake soup) which is the main food to eat on the new year. Have a bowl of it and claim that you are officially an year older (and wiser) - which is really a thing Koreans do. I'll try to have a vegan version too.
* I'll have 윷놀이yutnori game which is a Korean traditional game played on lunar new year. The goal is to have all four of your pieces travel around the map (like Monopoly) by throwing four sticks (aka 윷yut) in the air (which will determine how many steps you can take, similar to throwing dice). This becomes a strategy game because you can catch up to your opponent's piece and the caught piece needs to start from the start again; plus, you can stack your pieces and let multiple pieces travel together (you can go faster but more damage if you get caught)
* I also have 화투hwatoo for 고스톱GoStop if anyone wants to play card games. During last potluck we noticed that I'm missing a few cards so I bought a new deck.

The potluck part is optional. You can bring foods or drinks to share but you are not obligated to. It can be Korean or non-Korean. I know some people have dietary restrictions (no onions, vegan, etc.) so feel free to be considerate but it won't be necessary.

How to get to Haru's apartment: [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_STYNwtMRHmvwz14ju_8QPPyMz92greS/view?usp=drive_link](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_STYNwtMRHmvwz14ju_8QPPyMz92greS/view?usp=drive_link)

node.description:
It's been awhile since I hosted a potluck so let's do it again (EDIT: I scheduled this before I scheduled "Potluck + Goodbye Joon Dinner")

Cook something to share with others. It can be Korean or non-Korean foods. I know some people have dietary restrictions (no onions, vegan, etc.) so feel free to be considerate but it won't be necessary (we know some foods taste good if you put everything in it). If you are really crushed on time, then fruit or veggie platter (or chips) from a grocery store is an option.

* You may try my electric drum too lol
* And hang out with people!
* EDIT: This is pepero day in Korea! Feel free to bring some to share

About my place:

* My apartment is at Austin Parke apartment. It is the third floor of building 6 (the leasing office building). If you've never been here before, check out the attached photos for help. Or you can message me.
* There's no visitor parking rule so you can park wherever.
* My place is one bedroom apartment. I don't have a lot of chairs so most people are likely to sit on the hard floor. Shoes off plz too.
* I'll have (disposable) plates, cups, eating utensils ready.

node.title: Fight Back! IFA Women’s Self Defense Seminar (FREE)
node.description:
Join us Tuesday, October 17, 2023, at IFA Academy for Fight Back! This event is FREE to the public! Please SHARE THIS EVENT with your friends and ask them to share it with their friends as well. Learn how to fight and defend yourself with the proven effective methods of Boxing, Muay Thai, and Jiu Jitsu.

Limited spaces are available so please respond (by FB messenger or in this FB event page) that you are attending and how many people are in your group.

We began offering these seminars for women six years ago in response to the rising crime rate in Austin and alarming increase in violence and sexual assault against women. If you want to learn how to defend yourself, gadgety self defense techniques will not work. You must learn how to fight. This is a practical, proven, no-nonsense approach to self defense and it’s also a lot of fun!

IFA Academy is the longest running MMA (mixed martial arts) program in Central Texas, offering quality professional instruction in MMA, Boxing, Muay Thai, Jiu Jitsu, and Kali since 1990.

See you there!
